title.narrative: CHILD-SENSITIVE SOCIAL PROTECTION

description.narrative: Duty bearers can effectively measure, analyse and address social and economic vulnerabilities to poverty and deprivation through child-sensitive social protection, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Access To Inclusive Social Protection (Covid), Reducing Child Poverty, Reducing Child Poverty (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: All boys and girls benefit from a child-centered enabling environment that advances children's rights and addresses the effects of poverty, adversity and exclusion.
